The paper discusses a security protocol for RFID systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the security of the protocol. The authors also discuss the software engineering aspects (cs.SE) of the protocol and how it fails to provide proper security features. The paper also touches upon the cryptography (cs.CY) used in the protocol and how it is vulnerable to attacks. Finally, the paper involves the use of distributed computing (cs.DC) to analyze the security of the protocol.
